    "actor_description": "It still hurts, but the hurt stops hunting for new teeth. My chest loosens a fraction and I catch myself breathing all the way down, like my body finally believes it can. The sadness stays, heavy and honest, but it’s no longer dragging me under—more like a weight I can carry. For the first time in a while, the next hour feels possible.",
